Executive Profile
Joseph J. Grano Jr.Vice Chairman of Advisory Group, Amerityre CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 15 Board Members in 15 different organizations across 21 different industries.See Board Relationships69--
Background

		Dr. Joseph J. Grano, Jr., also known as Joe, is Co-Founder of Ecological, LLC. Dr. Grano serves as the Chief Executive Officer of Centurion Holdings LLC. He is co-founder at Fieldpoint Private Bank & Trust in 2008. Dr. Grano served as the Chief Executive Officer at root9B Holdings, Inc. from May 20, 2014 to May 25, 2017. He serves as Chairman of Ecological, LLC. He has been Non-Executive Chairman of root9B Holdings, Inc. since May 25, 2017 and Director since 2013. He ... serves as an Advisor at Hotlist Media, Inc. He serves as Chairman of Centurion Holdings LLC. He serves as an Advisor of The Cue Ball Group, LLC. Dr. Grano also serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Academy Securities Inc. He serves as a Co-Chair of the Board of Visible Technologies, Inc. and Co-Chairman of the Board of Advisors of Web Image. Dr. Grano also serves as a Co-Chairman of Advisory Board of TSV Group, Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Night Operations Systems Inc., Root9B LLC and Zito Partners. He serves as a Member of Board of Advisors at IPSA Security Services LLC. Dr. Grano serves as a Member of the National Board of D.A.R.E. and a Member of the Board of Directors at Lenox Hill Hospital. Dr. Grano served as the President of Retail Sales and Marketing at PaineWebber from February 29, 1988 to December 1997. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Wealth Management USA Business at UBS AG. He joined the UBS AG Group Executive Board on January 1, 2001 and served as the Chief Executive Officer of UBS Financial Services Inc. until January 1, 2004. Dr. Grano was instrumental in helping to bring about the merger of PaineWebber with UBS in 2000. Prior to that, Dr. Grano was with Merrill Lynch for 16 years holding various senior management positions including Director of National Sales of Merrill Lynch Consumer Markets. He joined the firm in 1972. Dr. Grano also served for five years in the United States Special Forces. He has been a Vice Chairman and First Member of Advisory Group of Amerityre Corp. since September 22, 2004. Dr. Grano has been an Independent Director of Aevi Genomic Medicine, Inc. since March 15, 2013. Dr. Grano has been a Member of Advisory Board at IPSA International, Inc. since February 2008. He served as Chairman of root9B Holdings, Inc. from January 1, 2013 to May 25, 2017. Previously, he served as the Chairman of Wealth Management USA of UBS Group AG. Dr. Grano served as the Chairman and Director of UBS PaineWebber from 2001 to 2004. He was appointed by President George W. Bush in 2002 to serve as the Chairman of the Homeland Security Advisory Council and he served in this capacity until August 2005. Dr. Grano also served as the Chairman of the Board of Governors of NASD. He served as a Vice Chairman of the Queens College Foundation Board of Trustees and was on the Board of Directors of the YMCA. He served as Chairman of UBS Financial Services Inc. Dr. Grano served as a Director of Miniluxe, LLC and Pack Rat. He served as a Member of Advisory Board of Zen Pottery Equipment Inc. Dr. Grano served as a Non-Executive Director of Ethoca Limited. He served as a Director of UBS Wealth Management USA since 1993 and Wealth Management USA. Dr. Grano served as a Member of Advisory Board of Global Energy Holdings Group, Inc. since April 25, 2006. He has been named the industry's best retail marketing executive in a survey conducted by Investment Dealers' Digest. Dr. Grano has been one of the financial service industry's leading executives for over 30 years. He is involved in a wide range of educational and philanthropic endeavors. Dr. Grano holds an Honorary Doctor of Laws degree from both Pepperdine University and Babson College and an Honorary Doctor of Humane Letters Degree from Queens College.Read Full Background




